ownedRule.name: one-to-one associations must have aggregation on one side

ownedComment.body: One-to-one associations must have one side of the association indicating aggregation (aggregation defines the parent/owning entity).

specification.body: context SpringEntityAssociationEnd inv: one2One implies (composition or aggregation or otherEnd.composition or otherEnd.aggregation)

ownedRule.name: collection parameters must use named parameters

ownedComment.body: A collection type argument can only be specified when using named parameters, please set the 'hibernateQueryUseNamedParameters' namespace property to 'true' when attempting to use a collection as a query argument.

specification.body: context SpringQueryOperation inv: not useNamedParameters implies arguments -> forAll(not type.collectionType)
